solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int longestSubsequence(string s, int k) {
        int n = s.size();
        int zeros = 0;
        for (char c : s) if (c == '0') zeros++;

        long long val = 0;
        int len = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            if (s[i] == '0') {
                len++;
                continue;
            }
            int pos = n - 1 - i;
            if (pos >= 30) continue;
            long long add = 1LL << pos;
            if (val + add <= k) {
                val += add;
                len++;
            }
        }
        return len;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Count all zeros (they can always be included). Scan left-to-right, greedily adding ones only when the bit position keeps the total ≤ k. Skip ones beyond the 30th bit (2^30 > 1e9).

